ZH: 他为了获得利益而倒行逆施。
EN: He resorts to unscrupulous means for personal gain.

ZH: 这种行为是倒行逆施的。
EN: This behavior goes against the natural order.

ZH: 不要倒行逆施，这样只会带来更多的麻烦。
EN: Do not resort to backward measures, as it will only bring more trouble.

ZH: 政府不应该倒行逆施，而应该遵循法律法规。
EN: The government should not resort to underhanded tactics, but should follow the laws and regulations.

ZH: 公司因为倒行逆施而陷入法律纠纷。
EN: The company got into legal trouble due to their improper actions.

ZH: 这次行动属于倒行逆施，不被人们认可。
EN: This action is seen as a backward measure and is not approved by the public.

ZH: 他一直在倒行逆施，终将自食其果。
EN: He has been resorting to unscrupulous means and will eventually face the consequences.

ZH: 任何企图倒行逆施的行为都不会得逞。
EN: Any attempt to resort to backward measures will not succeed.

ZH: 她试图通过倒行逆施来达到自己的目的。
EN: She tries to achieve her goals through underhanded tactics.

ZH: 我们不能通过倒行逆施来解决问题。
EN: We cannot solve problems by resorting to unscrupulous means.

ZH: 政府的倒行逆施引发了公众的强烈反对。
EN: The government's underhanded tactics have sparked strong public opposition.

ZH: 他的倒行逆施导致了团队的解散。
EN: His improper actions led to the dissolution of the team.

ZH: 在这个社会，倒行逆施是不被允许的。
EN: In this society, resorting to unscrupulous means is not allowed.

ZH: 他的倒行逆施让他失去了大家的信任。
EN: His underhanded tactics have caused him to lose the trust of others.

ZH: 出于绝望，他开始了倒行逆施。
EN: Out of desperation, he resorted to underhanded tactics.

ZH: 如果倒行逆施成为习惯，最终会自食其果。
EN: If resorting to underhanded means becomes a habit, it will eventually backfire.

ZH: 领导者不应该以倒行逆施的方式来维护权力。
EN: Leaders should not maintain power through unscrupulous means.

ZH: 倒行逆施只会让事情更糟糕。
EN: Resorting to backward measures will only make things worse.

ZH: 他为了一己私利而倒行逆施。
EN: He resorts to underhanded tactics for personal gain.

ZH: 公司的倒行逆施导致了严重损失。
EN: The company's underhanded tactics resulted in significant losses.
